e>   Proposal regarding the dragons...</span><hr size=1> Since the naggy and vox lists are so long, I think the minimum time required to actually conduct a dragon raid should be cut to 24 hours rather than 48 hours.  This should work for these reasons.<br>
<br>
1) It will keep the list moving quicker<br>
<br>
2) It will allow mobs such as Ragefire to spawn more often if it is policy to kill Nagafen within 24 - 47.99 hours after he spawns, rather than 48 - 71.99 hours.<br>
<br>
3) Being as though that most raid crews carry people of levels 47 - 52, rather than the pre-kunark 45- 50.  The number of failed raids are significantly low.  And if a raid fails it is entirely the fault of the raid leadership for going after the mob with a weak raid crew or for not keeping the raid crew in order.<br>
<br>
4) A dragon raid should take no more than 4 hours to do if the raid leadership comes prepared and seriously tries to work the week before/the few days before and hit up their friends lists to see if they can get the required classes they need.  If a raid leader cannot get the required classes to kill the dragon they really have no business conducting the raid in the first place.  4 hours = weeknight capable raid, there really is no reason to have to wait for the weekend.<br>
<br>
5) Under most circumstances if a guild/indy is coming up on the list they *should* be preparing for the raid a few weeks beforehand, if not, then why the hell did they put themselves on the list in the first place?<br>
<br>
6) As some people have said the Brell rules are in place to help facilitate the interaction between guilds and other people.  Many people view that the dragon rotations are a complete joke.  Just because you have waited on the list for 6 months does not give you any special priveleges over the rest of the server.  Any guild that does their legwork correctly can figure out about a month in advance aprroximately what days they'll be hitting the dragon (give/take a week) with the margin of error coming down as each week passes.  If we work to compress this time frame a bit more people will be able to prepare a bit more and if need be can make any special out of game arrangemens they may need a week or two in advance.<br>
<br>
I thank everyone for thei time and criticism.<br>
<br>
Veldan Lionsfury<br>
52nd Level Paladin of Tunare<br>
Alat-Seldi <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/utwiggietymberwolf.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Twiggie Tymberwolf</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle><font color=#FFFF66>Board Moderator <img src=http://www.brellserilis.net/images/goldstartr.gif align=middle><br><font color=#A0B0E0>Slacker Shaman</font></span><br>  Posts: 1287<br> <font color=#CC9900>(6/28/01 12:17:04 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Proposal regarding the dragons...</span><hr size=1>  Most raiders kill them the first day they are allowed.  Having the option for two days makes it easier for guilds that do not have players that are able to play every night. It also allows second attempts due to unforseen wipe outs or other issues that are not controllable.  Forcing people to have 24 hours instead of 48 hours will not make the lists go any faster. The lists are long not because of the time between each of them but the amount of guilds that are on them.  I personally feel that the amount of lists you can be on needs to be reduced to one not two.  It was two back when we had 4 lists.  Now that we have 3 lists it needs to be changed.  But even if that is done, while each list will move faster, in order to get both dragons in it will still take just as long.  <br>
<br>
Its just a simple fact that there are too many small guilds for a rotation to work quickly.  So either people need to start forming alliances or they need to just sit back and wait.<br>
<br>
Perfect example is Silent Redemption and Watchers.  Both guilds could kill Dain, Vindicator, Klandicar, Zlandicar, and CT without each others help.  But they work together on each spawn.  Yeah its overkill but its fun hanging out with each other and everyone gets to join in on each raid.  <br>
<br>
If more guilds would form alliances and be on the lists together instead of separate it would move alot faster and you would need less and less outside sign ups for each raid.  But of course no one wants to share anything so it never happens.<br>
<br>
Making people kill Vox/Nagafen every 8th day (you can't easily kill them the 7th day as spawn varies by a few hours) instead of a few on the 9th would not significantly reduce the lists.<br>
<br>
Vox:<br>
<br>
39 slots x 8 days = ~42 weeks<br>
39 slots x 9 days = ~47 weeks<br>
<br>
I would guess half the raids take her the first night meaning actual time is<br>
<br>
39 slots x 8.5 days = ~45 weeks<br>
<br>
So forcing people to go on the first day would only save you 3 weeks total.<br>
<br>
Nagafen<br>
<br>
41 slots x 8 days = ~47 weeks<br>
41 slots x 9 days = ~53 weeks<br>
<br>
I would guess half the raids take him the first night meaning actual time is<br>
<br>
41 slots x 8.5 days = ~50 weeks<br>
<br>
So forcing people to go on the first day would only save you 3 weeks total.<br>
<br>
So as you can see you will only increase the turn around on the rotation by 3 weeks over the course of 10-11 months while forcing people to have a set day in which some, if not many, guild members may not be able to make it.  I would also suspect that it would cause more dragons not to die because of being forced to go on a day that does not work out well for many people.<br>
<br>
Sorry but in my opinion the little time saved does not out weigh the disadvantages caused to those on the list.<br>
<br>
My question is, how many are on the list for their 2nd, 3rd, 4th, etc time now?  And why are you there still? <br>
1) Is it for epic pieces for the bard/warrior/paladin in the guild?  <br>
2) Or is it for loot?  <br>
3) Or is it for just the ability to fight dragons?<br>
<br>
