<br>
As to the other issue, lvl 52 people not levelling: It's not as simple as laziness.  I think that it is much more about knowledge.  Joe Paladin/Bard/Warrior wants a scale.  He knows they drop off a dragon.  He reads the boards and finds post after post inviting randoms to help kill Naggy and Vox.  He sees NOTHING about Talendar or Servelious or any of those.  The little that he does find out is that they are random spawns that seem to be killed by large guilds - guilds that he is not a member of.<br>
<br>
Yes, Joe Paladin can level up to 55 and be capable of killing these Kunark dragons.  But he doesn't know that he'll get a chance to even try.  Joe then decides to take the slow but steady approach.  He knows he can kill Naggy, even if it takes forever.  He doesn't go to 55 because he may get there and find out that he never even sees a dragon again.<br>
<br>
I'd say, don't wait for email about those dragons.  Post it like mad.  The more people know about it, the more likely they will be to make the leap.<br>
