<br>
As for ignorance, I for one am ignorant of what it takes to organize a Talendar/any other Kunark dragon raid.  I hear rumors of being 55+ needed, I hear you need several groups of 55+.  I can't imagine coming to the message board and posting that I saw Tal up and asking for signups for a raid that night would generate enough response to kill a dragon.  I imagine it would be killed by an in game organized group in a more timely fashion.<br>
<br>
I believe that any ignorance exists is not of what mobs it takes to kill but of ignorance of the skills necessary to kill Kunark dragons, which I believe is Dunsters point.<br>
<br>
Please consider you are asking these Paladins to level from 52 to 55 (a time consuming task) before even having a shot at getting on a dragon raid from most accounts.  I believe that given the evolution of the Paladin epic and Verants choice to level cap, etc., that leveling to 55 in and of itself is a huge risk in getting your epic if you are in a small guild.<br>
<br>
Please don't confuse these choices with &quot;if someone is that ignorant of the epic they don't deserve it&quot;.  It is not a matter of lazniess or entitlement but one of a very real risk they may never get a chance versus a very boring but known chance.<br>
<br>
I think the most positive thing that could come out of this portion of the thread is to enlighten the community on the virtues of killing Kunark dragons for your Paladin buds who LoH you without a second thought versus an accusation that Paladins who stay at level 52 must be lazy or unworthy of their epics. <p>Mipsy Gigaflop 54 Vicar<BR>
