Would I like to get him his epic?  Sure.  It's a nice sword.<br>
Will I stop levelling him at level 52 just because he doesn't have it?  Not a chance.<br>
<br>
Fiery Defender:<br>
35/40 15 AC 20 Str 10 Sta 15 Wis 10 to all resists 70 HP 30 Mana<br>
Effect of Holy Shock<br>
I think you can also bash while equiped.<br>
<br>
The total stats are nice, but now that Velious is out, there are SO many more options for you.<br>
Here's a prime example:<br>
Massive Dragonclaw Shard:<br>
24/30 3wis 3int<br>
1h slash.<br>
Sarnak Battle Shield:<br>
25 AC 5 Str 5 Sta 10 MR 10 FR 10 CR 40 HP<br>
<br>
Shields sell for under 15k.<br>
I bought the sword from an SR auction for a sum of 42k.<br>
I've seen them sell another for somewhere in the 30k+ range.<br>
I've since seen another being sold because the owner got a better weapon.<br>
Sure, it comes off of Zlandicar, but he dies regularly, and there's already been at least 2 sold on Brell auction board.<br>
Is the damage output quite as much?  Not quite, but it's got a close ratio.  4:5 isn't that much worse than 7:8.  And you don't really lose much in the way of stats all round.<br>
So, for about 50k, you can BUY equipment of near epic quality.<br>
In the weeks and weeks and weeks you level 52 suckas are waiting around to get your books, you could be levelling up, getting loot, and buy the weapon combo I mentioned above in a fraction of the time.<br>
Other prime examples of things to get are the various brawlsticks or slashers from DN.  Lots of them drop per night.  You might not get the same stats and resists, but you can get a BETTER damage output from some of the weapons there.<br>
Anyone ever hear of a Granite Face Grinder?<br>
29/36 10str 10wis 10int.   This has the same ratio as the epic, and you can buy them for 15k in a snap of the fingers.<br>
<br>
If you are serious about getting your epic, you work at it.<br>
Talk to your friends.  Get them to help out.<br>
Talk to some guild leaders.  See if you can get help of a guild if a dragon you need should happen to spawn.<br>
If you don't have the friends to get your epic, you don't deserve the epic.<br>
Gor, Tal, and Sev only have 32k hps.  Wizards wizards wizards.  The lifespan from pull to kill of the dragon will be under 1 minute if you do it right.  Get info from people that have killed the dragons.<br>
 <p>=============================
<br>Juujuu Bigmojo
<br>60 Ogre Shaman
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uveldanlionsfury.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Veldan Lionsfury</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_fire.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Traveller of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 212<br> <font color=#CC9900>(7/1/01 9:20:24 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.brellserilis.net/images/posticons/beertr.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Proposal regarding the dragons...</span><hr size=1> Yes, I've been level 51 since about early April, I just recently dinged 52.  I am leveling slowly because I have been taking care of other things in game, such as leveling up my friends/ guildmates so we can raid the planes together, as we are all kinda putzy on leveling.  Not necessarily lazy, we hate fighting in pick up groups all the time and prefer to play with one another, or not at all.  I just needed to clarify that because I felt the tone of this thread has degenerated into who is the laziest player...  anyway to help get it back on track...  <br>
<br>
Also, I could really care less about my epic at this time.  I've always been a weapon and Shield type Paladin and absolutely hated being forced to pick up a two handed style because that's the way the pre-kunark weapon progression went (i'm not number crunching for maximum efectiveness I'm choosing what fits my play style and my vision of my character.  And I have gotten many compliments on my Frostbringer/Fearsome Shield Combo).<br>
<br>
I have placed Alat-Seldi on the naggy/vox lists, 1) as a joke, because we're going to be in DAoC by the time our number comes up, 2) if something does change on the list and our number comes up in a reasonable amount of time, it would be nice to kill the dragon in an effort to get some of our guildies their epic pieces or perhaps even a nice haste item for the tanks.  (you still can't argue about winning a RBB or CoF from a dragon), 3) once a strong continegnet of the guild moves beyond 53 I will have our guild removed (unlike so many of the other guilds that are abusing the system).<br>
<br>
Most raiders do not kill the dragons the first day they are allowed, the most recent naggy slaying is one of those instances and most of last month if someone thought they could push the dragon onto a weekend date they tried all they could.  (one group even violated the rules and went for 4 days.)  Especially with a Dragon such as Nagafen, being the PH for an Epic MoB, it's important that he be taken care of as soon as is possible.  Because Rez sticks are nice. =)<br>
<br>
You mentioned something about &quot;the advantages of speeding up the list by a few weeks over a few months does not out weigh the disadvantages caused to guilds who try and take dragons with a weak raid crew because 24 hours is not a long enough time to assemble a raid crew.&quot;  <br>
<br>
I completely disagree with you on this, ANY guild/indy that is on the lists should be looking at all times for people to help round out their raids.  If a guild is coming up on the list they should be tapping on their friends list and seeing who they can count on for the raid.  If a guild can't produce the necessary folks from their friends list and from friends of friends, I'm sorry, that happens.  Perhaps you should try for smaller game, go hit phinny he drops epic stuff.  I guess I'm looking at it from the perspective that just because you have waited on a list for 6 months does not give you any special priveleges on taking down the mob over any other guild that is on the list because they have also been waiting for 6 months.  <br>
<br>
Twiggie, you spoke about guilds signing up on the list as a group to take out the dragons.  With a 6 month wait you can't bet on the fact that the other guild you signed up with will still be around and the way I read the rules they discourage that sort of cooperation because if the guilds that would be sponsoring the raid change, that spot is deleted.  And it's not an issue of sharing, it's an issue of the list.  Since each guild is able to hold their own spot on the list, why bother signing up as a joint effort?  You bide your time and wait.  <br>
<br>
We need to have some sort of system in place to try and endorse cooperation, and shortening the window of opportunity, will force some raid leaders to say, hey we should ask &quot;such and such a guild that's high on the list if they'd like to join our raid, they've probably been prepping for it, and might be able to send over some folks we need.&quot;<br>
<br>
But in the end, I do agree with you on one point.<br>
<br>
The 1 week saved per month ratio (you used a conservative estimate, i'm taking a bit more liberal estimate on it) is not enough to really warrant a change, I agree the lists should be reduced to one guild spot for any one of the three lists.  I would be more than willing to take Alat-Seldi off of either Vox or Naggy in an effort to shorten the lists, but only when it becomes a policy of the server.  <br>
<br>
So how do we get the policy changed?<br>
<br>
Veldan Lionsfury<br>
52nd Level Paladin of Tunare<br>
